title: Pivotal games for Boise St, Memphis to be best in Group of 5
text: > Sports Pivotal games for Boise St, Memphis to be best in Group of 5 CORRECTS THAT MEMPHIS HAS THE THIRD LONGEST CONSECUTIVE STREAK BEHIND OHIO STATE AND TCU - FILE - In this Sept. 12, 2015, file photo, Memphis head coach Justin Fuente talks to quarterback Paxton Lynch (12) during an NCAA college football game against Kansas in Lawrence, Kan. Memphis has won 12 consecutive games over the last year, for the third longest active streak among all Football Bowl Subdivision teams behind Ohio State and TCU. (AP Photo/Charlie Riedel, File)
